TEXT -1368 3096 Left 2 !.param t_start = 4000m\n.param tran_window = 200m\n.param t_stop = {t_start + tran_window}\n.param step = 1 / {1000 * in_freq}\n.tran {step} {t_stop} {t_start} {step}
TEXT 6232 3296 Left 2 ;https://www.duncanamps.com/spice/loudspeakers/vint30.inc
TEXT -1360 3384 Left 2 !* ====================================================================\n* 🎸 COMPREHENSIVE GUITAR AMP DIAGNOSTICS (PREAMP & POWER AMP)\n* Topology change: Q9 removed. Q11 is now a standalone emitter follower\n* (TONE_OUT → C21 → Q11B; new bias divider 330k/110k; P3 master vol at output).\n* ====================================================================\n* --- 1. POWER SUPPLY RAILS & RIPPLE ---\n* Checks if the filter caps (C13, etc.) are sufficiently sizing down the AC ripple.\n.meas tran Vcc_mean AVG V(VCC)\n.meas tran Vcc_max MAX V(VCC)\n.meas tran Vcc_min MIN V(VCC)\n.meas tran Vcc_ripple PARAM (Vcc_max-Vcc_min)\n.meas tran Vraw_mean AVG V(N002)\n.meas tran Vraw_max MAX V(N002)\n.meas tran Vraw_min MIN V(N002)\n.meas tran Vraw_ripple PARAM (Vraw_max-Vraw_min)\n* --- 2. DC OPERATING POINTS (BIASING) ---\n* Verifies transistors aren't saturated/cutoff. The script will use these to calculate Vbe and Vce.\n* Preamp Transistors (Q8, Q10, Q11, Q12)   ; Q9 removed\n.meas tran Vq12b_mean AVG V(Q12B)\n.meas tran Vq12e_mean AVG V(Q12E)\n.meas tran Vq10b_mean AVG V(Q10B)\n.meas tran Vq10e_mean AVG V(Q10E)\n.meas tran Vq8b_mean  AVG V(Q8B)\n.meas tran Vq8e_mean  AVG V(Q8E)\n.meas tran Vq11b_mean AVG V(Q11B)         ; target ~12.2 V (new divider)\n.meas tran Vq11e_mean AVG V(Q11E)         ; target ~11.55 V (Vbe ≈ 0.65 V)\n* Power Amp Transistors (Q1-Q7)\n.meas tran Vq1b_mean AVG V(Q1B)\n.meas tran Vq1e_mean AVG V(Q1E)\n.meas tran Vq2b_mean AVG V(Q2B)\n* Vq2e_mean removed: Q2 emitter is hardwired to GND (would always FAIL).\n.meas tran Vq2c_mean AVG V(Q2C)\n.meas tran Vq6b_mean AVG V(Q6B)\n.meas tran Vq6c_mean AVG V(Q6C)           ; ADDED — needed by Vce_Q4 below\n.meas tran Vq6e_mean AVG V(Q6E)\n.meas tran Vq7b_mean AVG V(Q7B)\n.meas tran Vq7c_mean AVG V(Q7C)\n* --- 3. SIGNAL LEVELS & HEADROOM (MAX/MIN/RMS) ---\n* Detects clipping limits. PRE_SPEAKER should center exactly at VCC/2.\n.meas tran Vpickup_in_max MAX V(PICKUP_IN)\n.meas tran Vpickup_in_min MIN V(PICKUP_IN)\n.meas tran Vpickup_in_rms RMS V(PICKUP_IN)\n.meas tran Vtone_in_max MAX V(TONE_IN)\n.meas tran Vtone_in_min MIN V(TONE_IN)\n.meas tran Vtone_in_rms RMS V(TONE_IN)\n.meas tran Vtone_out_max MAX V(TONE_OUT)\n.meas tran Vtone_out_min MIN V(TONE_OUT)\n.meas tran Vtone_out_rms RMS V(TONE_OUT)\n* NEW: Q11 buffer headroom monitoring (Q11 now sees full TONE_OUT swing)\n.meas tran Vq11b_max MAX V(Q11B)\n.meas tran Vq11b_min MIN V(Q11B)\n.meas tran Vq11b_rms RMS V(Q11B)\n.meas tran Vq11e_max MAX V(Q11E)\n.meas tran Vq11e_min MIN V(Q11E)\n.meas tran Vq11e_rms RMS V(Q11E)\n.meas tran Vpreamp_out_max MAX V(PREAMP_OUT)\n.meas tran Vpreamp_out_min MIN V(PREAMP_OUT)\n.meas tran Vpreamp_out_rms RMS V(PREAMP_OUT)\n.meas tran Vpre_speaker_max  MAX V(PRE_SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vpre_speaker_min  MIN V(PRE_SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vpre_speaker_mean AVG V(PRE_SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vpre_speaker_rms  RMS V(PRE_SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vspeaker_max MAX V(SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vspeaker_min MIN V(SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Vspeaker_rms RMS V(SPEAKER)\n* --- 4. GAIN STAGING ---\n* Tracks the AC voltage multiplication at every block. Uses peak-to-peak to ignore DC offsets.\n.meas tran Gain_Pre_Stage1 PARAM (Vtone_in_max-Vtone_in_min)/(Vpickup_in_max-Vpickup_in_min)\n.meas tran ToneStack_Loss  PARAM (Vtone_out_max-Vtone_out_min)/(Vtone_in_max-Vtone_in_min)\n* NEW: decomposed Stage 2 (was Q9+Q11+P3, now just Q11 follower + P3)\n.meas tran Buffer_Gain_Q11 PARAM (Vq11e_max-Vq11e_min)/(Vq11b_max-Vq11b_min)   ; expect ≈ 0.99\n.meas tran MasterVol_Atten PARAM (Vpreamp_out_max-Vpreamp_out_min)/(Vq11e_max-Vq11e_min)\n* Aggregate kept for backward comparison with old logs:\n.meas tran Gain_Pre_Stage2  PARAM (Vpreamp_out_max-Vpreamp_out_min)/(Vtone_out_max-Vtone_out_min)\n.meas tran Gain_Total_Preamp PARAM (Vpreamp_out_max-Vpreamp_out_min)/(Vpickup_in_max-Vpickup_in_min)\n.meas tran Gain_PowerAmp     PARAM (Vspeaker_max-Vspeaker_min)/(Vpreamp_out_max-Vpreamp_out_min)\n.meas tran Gain_System_Total PARAM (Vspeaker_max-Vspeaker_min)/(Vpickup_in_max-Vpickup_in_min)\n* --- 5. DISTORTION, SYMMETRY & RINGING ---\n* .four checks for harmonic distortion. Excessive high-order harmonics often indicate parasitic oscillation/ringing.\n* Symmetry variables >1.05 or <0.95 indicate asymmetric clipping.\n.meas tran Clip_Sym_Preamp PARAM abs(Vpreamp_out_max/Vpreamp_out_min)\n.meas tran Clip_Sym_Power  PARAM abs(Vspeaker_max/Vspeaker_min)\n.four {in_freq} 15 10 V(PREAMP_OUT)\n.four {in_freq} 15 10 V(PRE_SPEAKER)\n.four {in_freq} 15 10 V(SPEAKER)\n* Transient timing checks (Sharp spikes/ringing will disrupt these triggers, acting as a stability flag)\n.meas tran Rise_Time TRIG V(SPEAKER)=0.1*Vspeaker_max RISE=1 TARG V(SPEAKER)=0.9*Vspeaker_max RISE=1\n.meas tran Fall_Time TRIG V(SPEAKER)=0.9*Vspeaker_min FALL=1 TARG V(SPEAKER)=0.1*Vspeaker_min FALL=1\n* --- 6. QUIESCENT CURRENTS & POWER DRAW ---\n* Ensures the output stage bias isn't drifting into thermal runaway (Target: ~40mA per your schematic notes).\n.meas tran I_Supply_mean AVG I(V2)\n.meas tran Power_Total_W PARAM abs(I_Supply_mean*47)\n.meas tran Iq6_bias AVG I(R16)\n.meas tran Iq7_bias AVG I(R17)\n.meas tran Output_Bias_mA PARAM abs(Iq6_bias)*1000\n* --- 7. RIPPLE & AC MAINS INTRUSION (50Hz Base) ---\n* Evaluates how much mains hum/ripple reaches the audio path\n.four 50 10 2 V(N002)\n.four 50 10 2 V(VCC)\n.four 50 10 2 V(PREAMP_OUT)\n.four 50 10 2 V(SPEAKER)\n.meas tran Iq_R16_real AVG I(R16) FROM 100m TO 200m\n.meas tran Iq_R17_real AVG I(R17) FROM 100m TO 200m\n.meas tran Iq_through_output PARAM (abs(Iq_R16_real)+abs(Iq_R17_real))/2*1000\n* Vbe / Vce sanity checks\n.meas tran Vbe_Q6  PARAM Vq6b_mean - Vq6e_mean\n.meas tran Vbe_Q7  PARAM Vq7b_mean                  ; FIXED: Q7 emitter is GND, so Vbe = V(Q7B)\n.meas tran Vbe_Q11 PARAM Vq11b_mean - Vq11e_mean    ; ADDED: target ≈ 0.65 V\n.meas tran Vce_Q4  PARAM Vq6c_mean - Vq6b_mean      ; now resolves (Vq6c_mean added in §2)\n.meas tran Vce_Q5  PARAM Vq7b_mean - Vq7c_mean\n* Tone-stack diode clipper diagnostics\n.meas tran Vtone_in_pk_pos MAX V(TONE_IN)\n.meas tran Vtone_in_pk_neg MIN V(TONE_IN)\n.meas tran diode_clip_pos PARAM (Vtone_in_pk_pos > 1.35)\n.meas tran diode_clip_neg PARAM (Vtone_in_pk_neg < -1.95)\n.meas tran Speaker_RMS_power AVG abs(V(SPEAKER)*I(R27))
TEXT 4072 1136 Left 2 ;Note that Vcc is disconnected: will be used just for debug purposes, to simulate an ideal power supply unit.
